main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted in Tampa, Florida by a B-29 crew and Eastern Airlines pilots on 8 February 1950.
interesting points: The object was reported to be rocket-shaped and moving at an estimated speed of over 2000 mph.,The object maintained a high altitude and a straight course while being observed.,Multiple witnesses, including two Eastern Airlines pilots and a Major from the USAF, reported the sighting with consistent descriptions.,The sighting was made in clear weather conditions with visibility reaching 15 miles.,No photographs or sketches of the object were taken during the sighting.
witness description: Eastern Airlines pilots and a Major from the USAF
